<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Ain't that the truth! </span>Normally when I enter one of the LDoN zones, I am one of the first in and I am still summoning and buffing when the group pulls their first one.  I don't buff alot either - Shrink, Haste, Proc, Dex and Brawn.  If there is a Shaman in the group, I ask them to do HoS or better.  The problem is that several of these spells are long casting, meaning the DPS warder and I provide is lacking during the time it takes to get all this up again.
<br />

<br />
I really haven't had a problem with pets in these zones anyway, EXCEPT when we had a mob that could gate.  While we thought the pets chasing this mob down was what aggro'd the zone, thinking afterward showed that the mob just dragged alot of his friends and when he got in range, pets took off after him, while his buddies came after the group.  This did cause problems, but is easily solvable by backing off as soon as the target gates.  I only pray that if and when this happens to you, you have an enchanter to stop the train on its tracks!<br />_________________<br /><center><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3" color="purple"><b><i>Elder Riveni Chakravanti</i></b></font><br><font size="2" color="black">Vah Shir Feral Beastmistress<br>Member of Lodestar<br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=486142">Profile</a><br></font></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
